==English==
===Etymology===
From French [[sucre]] ("sugar"), der. of Latin [[saccharum]] + [[-ose]] (meaning, "full of")
===Noun===
'''sucrose'''
#Table [[sugar]].
#A [[disaccharide]] with formula C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub>, consisting of two simple sugars, [[glucose]] and [[fructose]].

